HEADWORD: Transpeciate
<hw>Tran*spe"ci*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>trans-</ets> + L. <ets>species</ets> form.]</ety> <def>To change
from one species to another; to transform.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Power to <qex>transpeciate</qex> a man into a horse.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transpicuous</ent>⟦br⟧
